Blood was diluted with four volumes of calcium- and magnesium-free PBS and 20 μL of the resulting suspension was added to 200 μL of growth medium containing 5 μg/mL of either concanavalin A (ConA) or lipopolysaccharide (LPS) to induce blastogenesis and allow lymphocyte proliferation. After 48 h, MTT assay was performed and the stimulation index (SI) was calculated as per the following formula.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{SI}=\frac{{\mathrm{Abs}}_{\mathrm{stimulated}}}{{\mathrm{Abs}}_{\mathrm{unstimulated}}}; $$\end{document}SI=AbsstimulatedAbsunstimulated;

Thereafter, percent change (potentiation or suppression) in lymphocyte blastogenesis in response to a mitogen was calculated as follows:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ \mathrm{Percent}\ \mathrm{change}=\left(\frac{{\mathrm{SI}}_{\mathrm{test}}-{\mathrm{SI}}_{\mathrm{control}}}{{\mathrm{SI}}_{\mathrm{control}}}\right)\times 100\%; $$\end{document}Percent change=SItest−SIcontrolSIcontrol×100%;
